data.text: Grammy Award-winning artist Nelly Furtado returned home to British Columbia, Canada and put on a great show for the 500+ people that attended. The smaller venue Commodore Ballroom is a step down for an artist of Nelly Furtado’s caliber, but she took full advantage of the up-close and intimate setting by rocking the house with her hits like “I’m Like a Bird”, “Say It Right” and “Promiscuous Girl”. Additionally, she performed songs off her latest album “The Spirit Indestructible” which includes the fan favorite album track “Spirit Indestructible”. Nelly Furtado obviously isn’t on the same platform she was back in 2006 when she was essentially on top of the Pop world, but there’s no doubt that she is still one of the most talented artists in the industry.
